Pour the @water{300%ml} into a large #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Tip in the @basmati rice{150%g}, bring to the boil, reduce the heat to medium and cover with a #lid{}. Cook for ~rice cooking{10%minutes}, then remove from the heat and set aside (still covered) for another ~rice resting{10%minutes}.

> TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam.

Meanwhile, pop the @pork strips{280%g} into a #mixing bowl{} with the @cornflour{10%g} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @ground black pepper{pinch}. Mix well. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Remove the top and bottom from the @carrot{1}(halved lengthways) (no need to peel!), halve lengthways and slice into thin half moons. Halve, then remove the core from the @green pepper{1} and cut into thin slices. In a #small bowl{}, stir together the @tomato ketchup{1%tbsp}, @soy sauce{25%g}, @water{50%ml} and @rice vinegar{15%ml}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Once hot, add the pork and stir-fry until golden all over, ~pork stir-frying{3-4%minutes}. Add the carrot and pepper and cook until slightly softened, another ~veg cooking{2%minutes}.

Lower the heat, then pour the sauce into the pan. Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until the pork is cooked through and the sauce is thick and glossy, ~sauce thickening{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The pork is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle. If it gets a bit dry just add a splash of water!

Fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and gently stir through the @coconut powder{50%g}.

Serve the coconutty rice in #bowls{} topped with the pork stir-fry. Enjoy!